Create a remote connection using the Oracle Eloqua connector to sync data from Oracle Eloqua to CRM Analytics.

To create the connection:

* Click New Connection on the Data Manager Connections tab.
* Click the name of the connector and click Next.
* Enter the connector settings:
	+ Connection Name: Identifies the connections.
	+ Developer Name: API name for the connection.
	+ Description: Description of the connection for internal use.
	+ Base URL: URL to connect to the Eloqua application.
	+ Username: User name for the Eloqua account.
	+ Time Zone Offset: Time zone in the Eloqua system settings relative to GMT.
	+ Domain Name: Company name for the Eloqua account, used at Eloqua sign-in.
	+ Password: Password for the Eloqua account.

Considerations:

* Connected object names must start with a letter and contain only letters, digits, or underscores.
* This connector can sync up to 10 million rows or 5 GB per object, whichever limit it reaches first.
* Object names must not contain special characters, such as spaces.
title: Connecting Oracle Eloqua to CRM Analytics
